<title>USA: SystemSoft to acquire Radish, book charge.</title>
<headline>SystemSoft to acquire Radish, book charge.</headline>
<dateline>NATICK, Mass. 1996-12-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>SystemSoft Corp said late Thursday that it has agreed to acquire Radish Communications Systems Inc, a privately held software supplier and developer of VoiceView, an industry standard for integrated voice and data communications, in exchange for 2.2 million shares of common stock valued at about $39 million.</p>
<p>SystemSoft said that the acquisition will result in charges to earnings during the fourth quarter estimated to be $41 million, or $1.52 per share.</p>
<p>The company said it anticipates that the transaction will close by December 31, 1996.</p>
